COVID-19 Resources

Reliable information about the coronavirus (COVID-19) is available from the World Health Organization (current situation Link: https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/situation-reports , international travel Link: https://www.who.int/news-room/articles-detail/updated-who-recommendations-for-international-traffic-in-relation-to-covid-19-outbreak/ ). Numerous and frequently-updated resource results are available from this WorldCat.org search Link: /search?qt=worldcat_org_all&q=covid-19#x0%253Aartchap-%2C%2528x0%253Aartchap%2Bx4%253Adigital%2529%2C%2528x0%253Aartchap%2Bx4%253Achptr%2529%2C%2528x0%253Abook%2Bx4%253Adigital%2529%2C%2528x0%253Avideo%2Bx4%253Adigital%2529%2C%2528x0%253Ajrnl%2Bx4%253Adigital%2529%2C%2528x0%253Aarchv%2Bx4%253Adigital%2529%2C%2528x0%253Aweb%2Bx4%253Adigital%2529format . OCLC’s WebJunction has pulled together information and resources Link: https://www.webjunction.org/news/webjunction/libraries-and-the-coronavirus.html to assist library staff as they consider how to handle coronavirus issues in their communities.
